node.text:
Feat Hafiz, our boulster+ beneficiary at the recent National Schools Sport Climbing Competition. First time at it and a finalist too! üèÜ
***
The boulster+ Programme is a pay-it-forward initiative to share the joys and benefits of bouldering. 
To date, 165 passes have been sponsored and used for this worthy cause and we would like to say a BIG THANK YOU to all the kind souls out there! 
Beneficiaries include domestic helpers, children with special needs and our 3 ‚Äòadoptive‚Äô sons: Hifzhan, Arash and Hafiz. For the past year, they have stuck to the rigors of the sport, experienced the warmth, kindness and friendship of the b+ community and have evolved into happy, friendly and strong boulderers. 
As b+ enters our 2nd year, we would like to canvass for more sponsors to come onboard to donate more boulster+ Passes (link in bio!) For each pass donated, b+ will match it one for one. Sponsors are welcome to suggest new beneficiaries or better still arrange a date where both sponsor and beneficiary can boulder together. 
Thank you in advance and keep the good vibes going at b+! ‚ô•Ô∏è

Thanks guys and hope their corny video (swipe!!!) chases away whatever is left of your Monday blues üôÜüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Mighty pleased to have initiated 30 people into our b+ fam. Nothing like building this community and growing this family with you all. Stay tuned for more development and deals just for you, fam ‚ô•Ô∏è

Tonight we bid farewell to Khai aka Mot who is leaving us to try his hands at something new altogether. Khai has been an integral part of the team since Day 1 - from screwing on struts on the wall structure and being part of the massive reno clean up to route setting, coaching and being an all-round fun chap to hang out with. We will still see him around when he‚Äôs back in town but b+ isn‚Äôt gonna be the same without our dearest abang Khai üò≠üò≠üò≠ *cue for sad music*
